1.5    Accidental Release Prevention Program and Process Safety Information (Appendix B)

COSL maintains a variety of technical documents that are used to help ensure safe operations of the WWTP and WTP processes.  These documents address the physical properties of hazardous substances handled at their facilities, operating parameters of the systems, and equipment operating procedures for these processes.  COSL ensures that this process safety information is available to its employees and the fire protection district, which serves as the local emergency response team.

International Chemical Safety Cards are produced by the international safety community and are cosponsored by the National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health (NIOSH).  This resource is intended to provide health and safety information for workers potentially in contact with these chemicals.  The International Chemical Safety Cards for chlorine and sulfur dioxide are provided in Appendix B. 

